{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.19",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 19 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:1",
      "text": "Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his lips and is a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:2",
      "text": "It isn’t good to have zeal without knowledge, nor to be hasty with one ’s feet and miss the way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:3",
      "text": "The foolishness of man subverts his way; his heart rages against Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:4",
      "text": "Wealth adds many friends, but the poor is separated from his friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:5",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished. He who pours out lies shall not go free.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:6",
      "text": "Many will entreat the favor of a ruler, and everyone is a friend to a man who gives gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:7",
      "text": "All the relatives of the poor shun him; how much more do his friends avoid him! He pursues them with pleas, but they are gone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:8",
      "text": "He who gets wisdom loves his own soul. He who keeps understanding shall find good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:9",
      "text": "A false witness shall not be unpunished. He who utters lies shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:10",
      "text": "Delicate living is not appropriate for a fool, much less for a servant to have rule over princes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:11",
      "text": "The discretion of a man makes him slow to anger. It is his glory to overlook an offense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:12",
      "text": "The king ’s wrath is like the roaring of a lion, but his favor is like dew on the grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:13",
      "text": "A foolish son is the calamity of his father. A wife’s quarrels are a continual dripping.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:14",
      "text": "House and riches are an inheritance from fathers, but a prudent wife is from Yahweh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:15",
      "text": "Slothfulness casts into a deep sleep. The idle soul shall suffer hunger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:16",
      "text": "He who keeps the commandment keeps his soul, but he who is contemptuous in his ways shall die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:17",
      "text": "He who has pity on the poor lends to Yahweh; he will reward him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:18",
      "text": "Discipline your son, for there is hope; don’t be a willing party to his death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:19",
      "text": "A hot-tempered man must pay the penalty, for if you rescue him, you must do it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:20",
      "text": "Listen to counsel and receive instruction, that you may be wise in your latter end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:21",
      "text": "There are many plans in a man ’s heart, but Yahweh ’s counsel will prevail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:22",
      "text": "That which makes a man to be desired is his kindness. A poor man is better than a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:23",
      "text": "The fear of Yahweh leads to life, then contentment; he rests and will not be touched by trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:24",
      "text": "The sluggard buries his hand in the dish; he will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:25",
      "text": "Flog a scoffer, and the simple will learn prudence; rebuke one who has understanding, and he will gain knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:26",
      "text": "He who robs his father and drives away his mother is a son who causes shame and brings reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:27",
      "text": "If you stop listening to instruction, my son, you will stray from the words of knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:28",
      "text": "A corrupt witness mocks justice, and the mouth of the wicked gulps down iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.19.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 19:29",
      "text": "Penalties are prepared for scoffers, and beatings for the backs of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
